WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:07.000
Marcel and the Mona Lisa by Stephen Rabley

00:07.300 --> 00:13.800
Marcel is a French mouse and a detective. He has lots of friends in Paris.

00:13.800 --> 00:18.280
One of them is Céline. She paints pictures

00:18.280 --> 00:21.720
and is very beautiful. Céline's home

00:21.720 --> 00:26.520
is at the Louvre. Marcel often goes there for dinner.

00:26.520 --> 00:30.800
One evening in May he arrives with some pink flowers.

00:30.800 --> 00:35.000
There is a guard at the door. I don't know him.

00:35.000 --> 00:38.080
Marcel thinks he must be new.

00:38.080 --> 00:41.800
Then he walks inside. The two friends

00:41.800 --> 00:48.160
eat, drink and talk all evening. Céline shows Marcel her new paintings.

00:48.160 --> 00:52.200
They talk about their summer holidays in Los Angeles.

00:52.200 --> 00:55.600
They laugh, play jazz records

00:55.760 --> 00:59.160
and tell lots of stories. Then

00:59.160 --> 01:02.960
at eleven o'clock Marcel puts on his coat.

01:02.960 --> 01:07.040
It's late, he says. I must go home.

01:07.040 --> 01:10.040
Two minutes later he leaves.

01:10.040 --> 01:14.360
Well good night, Céline, then she closes her front door.

01:14.360 --> 01:17.520
Marcel walks across the floor.

01:17.520 --> 01:20.520
He's very happy. Then he stops.

01:20.520 --> 01:23.920
The room is dark but he can see

01:23.960 --> 01:27.280
something. What is it? A man?

01:27.280 --> 01:29.840
A man with a long knife?

01:29.840 --> 01:32.760
Yes! Suddenly

01:32.760 --> 01:36.520
Marcel's mouth is very dry. He runs to the wall.

01:36.520 --> 01:39.480
Then after five seconds he looks again.

01:39.480 --> 01:42.800
This time he can see the man's face.

01:42.800 --> 01:46.160
It's that new guard, he thinks.

01:46.160 --> 01:49.400
And he's stealing the man.

01:50.400 --> 01:54.240
Next to the thief there is a black bag.

01:54.240 --> 01:58.800
Two minutes later the Mona Lisa is inside it.

01:58.800 --> 02:02.040
The thief smiles and picks up the bag.

02:02.040 --> 02:04.760
But a second later he puts it down again.

02:04.760 --> 02:07.840
Carkey!

02:07.840 --> 02:12.000
He says and begins to look in all his pockets.

02:12.000 --> 02:14.880
All right.

02:15.040 --> 02:17.320
This is it, Marcel thinks.

02:17.320 --> 02:19.560
It is now or never.

02:19.560 --> 02:21.920
He runs along the wall very fast,

02:21.920 --> 02:26.760
climbs up the tall black bag and jumps inside it.

02:26.760 --> 02:31.160
At the bottom of the bag, Marcel can see a face.

02:31.160 --> 02:33.280
The Mona Lisa's face.

02:33.280 --> 02:36.520
She's smiling at him.

02:36.520 --> 02:39.280
Now what? He asks her.

02:39.280 --> 02:42.160
There is no answer, but at that moment

02:42.240 --> 02:45.160
the bag starts to move.

02:45.160 --> 02:48.640
Marcel can hear lots of noises.

02:48.640 --> 02:50.360
A motor starts.

02:50.360 --> 02:52.720
Traffic goes by.

02:52.720 --> 02:54.600
A radio plays.

02:54.600 --> 02:57.520
Then the bag suddenly stops.

02:57.520 --> 03:00.920
Marcel climbs the painting and looks out.

03:00.920 --> 03:03.920
El West de Champs.

03:03.920 --> 03:09.080
Five minutes later the Louvre Guard gets on the train.

03:09.080 --> 03:15.080
He sits next to a thin man in sunglasses and a white jacket.

03:18.080 --> 03:20.720
Have you got it, Antoine?

03:20.720 --> 03:25.240
The thin man asks, the guard answers.

03:25.240 --> 03:29.680
After that the train starts and there is a lot of noise.

03:29.680 --> 03:30.840
Oh no.

03:30.840 --> 03:33.960
Now I can't hear them, Marcel thinks.

03:33.960 --> 03:37.960
But he can hear one or two words.

03:37.960 --> 03:43.400
Italy, for example, and all those cats.

03:43.400 --> 03:45.040
Cats.

03:45.040 --> 03:47.400
Marcel looks at the Mona Lisa.

03:47.400 --> 03:51.000
His eyes are two big saucers.

03:51.000 --> 03:54.440
But cats can kill mice.

03:54.440 --> 03:55.960
He thinks.

03:55.960 --> 03:57.760
They eat them.

03:57.760 --> 03:59.840
And what are we going?

03:59.840 --> 04:01.920
Where are we going in Italy?

04:01.920 --> 04:03.960
Rome.

04:03.960 --> 04:06.480
Milano Napoli.

04:06.480 --> 04:12.320
But at that moment, Antoine puts the bag under the seat.

04:12.320 --> 04:16.480
Now I really can't hear, Marcel thinks.

04:16.480 --> 04:22.680
Then he goes to sleep and has a very bad dream.

04:22.680 --> 04:26.280
Early next morning the sun is shining.

04:26.280 --> 04:29.960
Marcel opens his eyes and sees the Mona Lisa.

04:29.960 --> 04:32.520
Then he remembers where he is.

04:32.520 --> 04:38.400
He runs up the painting and looks at Antoine and Auri.

04:38.400 --> 04:39.760
Good.

04:39.760 --> 04:42.040
He thinks, they are asleep.

04:42.040 --> 04:45.960
Ten seconds later, Marcel is standing at the window.

04:45.960 --> 04:49.960
He can see a small village and some mountains.

04:49.960 --> 04:57.720
Then a sign goes by 180 kilometers to Venice.

04:57.720 --> 05:02.680
Two hours later, Antoine and Auri are on a gondola.

05:06.040 --> 05:09.920
Look, says Antoine, and laughs.

05:09.920 --> 05:12.280
He shows Auri a newspaper story.

05:12.280 --> 05:15.960
It says thieves take Da Vinci painting.

05:19.000 --> 05:21.840
Auri says be quiet.

05:21.840 --> 05:25.280
It turns to the boatmen.

05:25.280 --> 05:27.920
Do you see that big palace on the left?

05:27.920 --> 05:32.360
Signor Spandini's house.

05:32.360 --> 05:35.640
Yes, stop there.

05:35.640 --> 05:41.200
Inside the bag, Marcel hears every word.

05:41.200 --> 05:44.080
An old woman answers the front door.

05:44.080 --> 05:48.720
Come in, she says, to the two thieves.

05:48.720 --> 05:53.400
Signor Spandini is waiting for you.

05:53.400 --> 05:55.960
She takes them to a big dark room.

05:55.960 --> 05:58.520
A fat man is sitting behind a desk.

05:58.520 --> 05:59.880
A desk.

05:59.880 --> 06:03.600
However you got it, he asks.

06:03.600 --> 06:06.680
Yes, boss.

06:06.680 --> 06:07.880
Henry answers.

06:07.880 --> 06:09.720
The bag is beside him.

06:09.720 --> 06:12.960
I cannot stay here, Marcel thinks.

06:12.960 --> 06:17.880
He jumps out of the bag and hides behind a chair.

06:17.880 --> 06:19.520
Good, he thinks.

06:19.520 --> 06:23.240
Now I can, but then he goes cold.

06:23.240 --> 06:25.800
Oh, cats.

06:25.800 --> 06:28.880
There are seven, eight.

06:28.880 --> 06:31.320
No, nine of them in the room.

06:31.320 --> 06:37.000
Suddenly, Marcel remembers Auri's words.

06:37.000 --> 06:40.120
Oh, those cats.

06:40.120 --> 06:42.520
Then he remembers his dream on the train.

06:42.520 --> 06:43.880
What can he do?

06:43.880 --> 06:45.320
Where can he go?

06:45.320 --> 06:46.600
But it's too late.

06:46.600 --> 06:49.080
One of the cats sees him.

06:49.160 --> 06:50.160
Help!

06:50.160 --> 06:54.640
Marcel thinks and climbs up the red curtain.

06:54.640 --> 06:58.440
A moment later, the cats start climbing too.

06:58.440 --> 07:00.640
Marcel can hear it below him.

07:00.640 --> 07:02.840
He has to do something and fast.

07:02.840 --> 07:04.080
But what?

07:04.080 --> 07:07.360
Then he sees two candles above his head.

07:07.360 --> 07:09.800
That's the answer, he thinks.

07:09.800 --> 07:12.560
He jumps onto the bookcase and starts

07:12.560 --> 07:15.120
to push the candles over.

07:15.120 --> 07:19.000
They're heavy, but in the end, he

07:19.000 --> 07:20.240
does it.

07:20.240 --> 07:24.160
Below him, he hears, yow, yow, yow.

07:27.600 --> 07:29.360
What is all that noise?

07:29.360 --> 07:32.360
As sent one.

07:32.360 --> 07:35.080
Look, the carpet's on fire.

07:35.080 --> 07:36.720
Says Auri.

07:36.720 --> 07:38.480
Spandini stands up.

07:38.480 --> 07:42.680
Angelina, a quick, bring some water.

07:42.680 --> 07:44.640
Marcel looks over the bookcase.

07:44.640 --> 07:48.400
He can see the Mona Lisa on Spandini's desk.

07:48.400 --> 07:49.920
OK, he thinks.

07:49.920 --> 07:51.400
This is it.

07:51.400 --> 07:54.080
After that, he runs down the curtain.

07:54.080 --> 07:58.200
Across Spandini's desk, picks up the Mona Lisa

07:58.200 --> 08:01.160
and runs out of the room.

08:01.160 --> 08:03.840
Marcel runs for a long time.

08:03.840 --> 08:08.280
He thinks, I want to leave the Mona Lisa somewhere safe,

08:08.280 --> 08:09.960
but where?

08:09.960 --> 08:14.400
Then, after 20 minutes, he stops in a quiet street.

08:14.400 --> 08:17.440
In front of him, there is a police station.

08:17.440 --> 08:19.760
The front door has a letterbox.

08:19.760 --> 08:22.960
Of course, Marcel thinks, that's it.

08:22.960 --> 08:26.320
He stands up tall, then he pushes the Mona Lisa

08:26.320 --> 08:29.240
through the letterbox.

08:29.240 --> 08:32.760
Two days later, Marcel is in Paris again.

08:32.760 --> 08:35.280
At the station, he sees a newspaper.

08:35.280 --> 08:40.280
It says, Italian police, find the Mona Lisa.

08:40.280 --> 08:44.640
Then, he goes to the Louvre and tells Silly and everything.

08:44.640 --> 08:46.840
Oh, nine cats.

08:46.840 --> 08:52.320
She says, oh, Marcel, are you all right?

08:52.320 --> 08:55.200
Yes, I am fine, Marcel answers.

08:55.200 --> 08:57.680
He goes to Celine's window.

08:57.680 --> 09:01.720
And the Mona Lisa is fine too.

09:01.720 --> 09:04.120
Look, Celine, she's smiling.

